Hi,

the idle injection belongs to the powercap subsystem and we may want to
inject a specific idle state (eg. retention or CPU power down instead of
cluster power down), currently we choose the deepest idle state. The
in-kernel change will be trivial as we can pass an idle state to the
play_idle function.

However, how can we specify that from userspace?

The powercap zones are exported in sysfs and the constraint files are
predefined.

Would it make senses to create a 'param' file as a generic ABI taking
"<param>=<value>" pair and let the underlying powercap zone backend to
interpret it?

eg:

 echo "idle=1" > param




